Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of network calculus theory to Time-Sensitive Networking (TSN) and Deterministic Networking (DetNet), which are both related to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with delay guarantee analysis, which is a topic in control systems and system theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), distributed computing (cs.DC), and programming languages (cs.PL) to some extent.
